| HistoryText             = The '''Nasty Boys''' were the personal strike force of [[Nathaniel Essex (Earth-616)|Mister Sinister]].{{Citation}}

[[X-Factor (Government) (Earth-616)|X-Factor]] battled the Nasty Boys{{r|X-Factor #75}} after [[Christopher Anderson (Earth-616)|Slab]] initially attacked [[Guido Carosella (Earth-616)|Strong Guy]].{{r|X-Factor #74}} 

[[James Madrox (Earth-616)|Multiple Man]] was able to subdue [[James Madrox (Fallen Angels) (Earth-616)|his dupe]].{{r|X-Factor #75}} 

Sinister posed as [[Steven Shaffran (Earth-616)|Steven Shaffran]] and unveiled his plan to kill the [[Wanda Maximoff (Earth-616)|Scarlet Witch]]. Shraffan, angered, attempted to kill him, only to be killed himself.{{r|X-Factor #75}} 

[[Patrick Mahony (Earth-616)|Ramrod]] was deported but returns illegally. Slab worked for the [[Mutant Liberation Front (Earth-616)|MLF]] alongside his sister [[Kristina Anderson (Earth-616)|Thumbelina]].{{r|X-Men Vol 2 #15}} 

The team was later regrouped by Sinister. They hunted [[Alice MacAllister (Earth-616)|Malice]] who was seeking to kill [[Lorna Dane (Earth-616)|Polaris]] so they could not re-merge. They left after Malice was apparently destroyed by Polaris and [[Alexander Summers (Earth-616)|Havok]].{{r|X-Factor #104|105}}

[[Clement Wilson (Earth-616)|Ruckus]] was apprehended during an attempted attack on [[Robert Kelly (Earth-616)|Senator Kelly]].{{r|X-Men Forever Vol 1 1}}

Much later, the team decided to reform during the final days of mutantkind, after [[X-Men Disassembled|X-Man’s return that ended in the death of most of the X-Men]]. It was revealed to be bait set up by the [[Upstarts (Earth-616)|Upstarts]] to lure out the remaining X-Men. They were all promptly murdered by the Upstarts.{{r|Uncanny X-Men Vol 5 20}}

